<HEADLINE> OPEC Cuts Oil Output by 1 mln bpd in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 11 (Xinhua) -- Oil production of the members of the
Organization of the Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) stood at
27.95 million barrels per day (bpd) in April, 1.03 million bpd
less than in February, according to the International Energy
Agency (IEA) Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Paris-based agency said in its monthly oil market report
that last month, OPEC has implemented most of the production cuts
it pledged in the March output cuts deal in an effort to help
rescue oil price on the world market.
</P>
<P>
OPEC's April output cut was 80 percent of the 1.25 million bpd
cut from April 1 it agreed in a deal signed in March with non-OPEC
producers to reduce world production by two percent and it helped
remove some of the second quarter oil surplus, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the agency cut its 1998 non-OPEC oil supply forecast
to 45.1 million bpd by 200,000 bpd, which is another factor for
the world oil market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
