<HEADLINE> Russian Upper House of Parliament Chairman to Visit France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 11 (Xinhua) -- The chairman of the Russian Federal
Council or Upper House of the Russian Parliament, Egor Stroyev,
will pay an official visit to France from May 11 to 14 at the
invitation of the president of French Senate Rene Monory.
</P>
<P>
The French Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Anne Gazeau-Secret said
on Monday that Stroyev will meet with Prime Minister Lionel Jospin
and the National Assembly speaker Laurent Fabius, as well as
representatives of the French enterprises.
</P>
<P>
"The French and Russian parliaments maintain close
cooperations. Mr. Stroyev will be accompanied by a big delegation
of representatives of the republics and regions who hope to
develop relations, especially economic relations, with France and
its regions," said Gazeau-Secret.  
</P>
