<HEADLINE> APEC Secretariat's Executive Director Visits Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, May 11 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of Vietnam's National
Assembly Nong Duc Manh said here Monday that he hopes APEC will
continue assisting his country's effective participation in APEC's
activities once Vietnam becomes a full member of the organization.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnam News Agency said Manh made the remark while meeting
Noor Adland, executive director of the Secretariat of the
Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC), who arrived earlier for
a six-day visit.
</P>
<P>
Manh welcomed Adlan's visit as a manifestation of the goodwill
between himself and APEC in helping Vietnam join the organization.
</P>
<P>
He said, in the ongoing renovation drive, Vietnam attaches
importance to expanding its relations and cooperation with other
countries, and international as well as regional organizations for
peace, independence and development.
</P>
<P>
Noor Adlan said he was glad to see that Vietnam would join APEC
this November. He described it as a success of not only Malaysia,
the host country of the coming APEC session, but also of the whole
organization.
</P>
<P>
The APEC official spoke highly of Vietnam's application for
entry into the organization and stressed that APEC mainly works to
boost the cooperation, equality and development among member
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
