<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Gross Reserves Fall in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, May 11 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's total gold and
foreign exchange reserves fell marginally to 32.72 billion Rand
(6.48 billion U.S. Dollars) in April, the Reserve Bank said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The reserves dropped 81.36 million Rand (16.1 million Dollars)
from the historic high of 32.8 billion Rand (6.5 billion Dollars)
in March, South African Press Association quoted the bank as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The decline surprised the markets which had expected reserves
to rise to at least 34 billion Rand (6.73 billion Dollars) on the
back of net purchases of 12.7 billion Rand (2.5 billion Dollars)
of South African equities and bonds by foreigners during April.
</P>
<P>
In a monthly statement of assets and liabilities, the central
bank said gold reserves picked up from the March figure of 5.37
billion Rand (1.06 billion Dollars) to 5.48 billion Rand (1.09
billion Dollars).
</P>
<P>
But foreign assets fell by 196.34 million Rand (38.9 million
Dollars) from 27.43 billion Rand (5.43 billion Dollars) in March
to 27.23 billion (5.39 billion Dollars) in April.  
</P>
</TEXT>
