<HEADLINE> France Produces First Euro Coin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 11 (Xinhua) -- France Monday produced the world's
first coin of the European single currency euro at a monetary
establishment in Pessac near Bordeaux in southwest France,
announced the French government.
</P>
<P>
A ceremony to this effect was held in the presence of the
Minister of Finance Dominique Strauss-Kahn, who symbolically
pushed the button to strike the first coin of euro.
</P>
<P>
The one-euro coin resembles a 10-franc coin, with a yellow
crown and a white bronze heart. It has a tree of life inscribed in
one side, and a miniature of the European continent on the other.
</P>
<P>
France will start to produce the series of euro coins -- from
0.01 euro to two euros -- in several weeks, while Germany,
Belgium, Spain and Italy will also start producing the euro soon.
</P>
<P>
The euro, to be officially launched on January 1, 1999, will
not completely replace the national currencies until 2002.  
</P>
</TEXT>
