<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, May 11 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican Prime Minister
Pascoal Mocumbi said Monday there is no likelihood of changing
the country's electoral legislation before the municipal
elections scheduled for the end of June.
</P>
<P>
This is because bills should be submitted at least 45 days in
advance to the country's parliament for consideration, Southern
African Broadcasting Association quoted Mocumbi as saying.
</P>
<P>
