the voters' roll, the report said.
</P>
<P>
However, Mocumbi suggested there could be changes in the
electoral legislation, but only after the first round of polling
on 33 cities and towns on June 30.
</P>
<P>
He said the government has done everything in its power to
ensure as many as possible votes.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Mozambican President Joaquim Chissano Monday
reiterated his call on voters to take part in the municipal
elections, saying eligible voters should exercise their right to
choose their leaders.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a rally in the northwestern province of Tete,
Chissano said there was hope of a better future in people's
lives. 
