<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nuclear Power Covers Over One-Third of EU Energy Supply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 11 (Xinhua) -- About 36 percent of electricity used
in the 15 European Union (EU) countries were generated by nuclear
power plants in 1997, the German power plant association VDEW said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The electricity production in the EU states totalled 2,246
billion kilowatt-hours last year, including about 812 billion
kilowatt-hours delivered by nuclear power plants, VDEW said.
</P>
<P>
Eight of the 15 EU states currently have nuclear power plants,
with France leading the field with 78 percent of its energy supply
covered by nuclear power.
</P>
<P>
Spain and Germany came in second with a nuclear energy share of
32 percent, followed by Finland with 30 percent and Britain with
29 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
