<HEADLINE> Drunken Soldier Shot Dead Six People in S. Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, May 11 (Xinhua) -- A drunken soldier shot dead six
people and wounded three others Sunday night in southern
Gikongoro town, military sources in the area told Rwanda News
Agency Monday.
</P>
<P>
"He had been having beer with other fellow soldiers in a local
bar," a resident of Gikongoro said.
</P>
<P>
It is said that the drunken soldier, private Viateur
Nkurunziza started shooting at people at around 20:00 (local
time), beginning by his colleague with whom he was returning back
to the barracks, the Rwanda News Agency said.
</P>
<P>
The private went on a shooting spree killing anyone he met on
his way. Four bodies were later on retrieved by security forces
which intervened upon hearing a sudden gunfire roaring in town.
</P>
<P>
Three other people, one soldier and two civilians were also
wounded in the shooting. But residents in Gikongoro told RNA that
the death toll is much higher, talking of nine people killed, six
soldiers and three civilians.
</P>
<P>
It is said that the drunken soldier was shot dead by the same
security forces as he tried to resist being arrested.
</P>
<P>
Investigations in the bloody incident began immediately,
military sources in Gokongoro told RNA.  
</P>
</TEXT>
