<HEADLINE> Iranian President Urges Close ECO Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 11 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad Khatami
stated here Monday evening that serious cooperation among the
Economic Cooperation Organization (ECO) nations would be the
logical means to the development, advancement and strengthening of
regional security.
</P>
<P>
Returning from the one-day ECO summit in Almaty, Kazakhstan,
Khatami said that the heads of the ECO members in their meeting
decided to remove all executive obstacles in the way of the
establishment of educational institution and cultural activities.
</P>
<P>
