him as a Israeli agent to seek chances for a pardon, Israel has
always maintained that Pollard acted alone.
</P>
<P>
However, Israel last months reversed its attitude to decide to
work out a plan acknowledging Pollard as its agent.
</P>
<P>
Edelstein said Pollard will be informed of the decision Friday
and the plan is the official position of Israeli government.
