<HEADLINE> Frankfurt Stock Exchange to Extend Trading Hours </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 11 (Xinhua) -- The Frankfurt Stock Exchange Monday
said that it would extend its floor-trading session by five and a
half hours from July 1 this year to ensure fair competition.
</P>
<P>
Under the plan, which still needs to be approved by the stock
exchange's supervisory board, the new floor-trading session would
run from 8:30 to 17:00 instead of the current session from 10:30
to 13:30.
</P>
<P>
Analysts in Frankfurt said that the reform was mainly intended
to offset fierce competition from a newly installed electronic
stock trading system called Xetra as well as from regional stock
exchanges in Duesseldorf, Munich, Berlin, Stuttgart, Bremen,
Hamburg and Hanover. 
</P>
