<P>
The center, a fruit of the effort by both the Mozambican and
Chinese governments, is expected to make contribution to the
promotion of bilateral trade and economy between the two
countries, Shao Guanfu, Chinese Ambassador to Mozambique said.
</P>
<P>
Shao said that the two countries, with long history of
friendship, have great potential and bright future for
cooperation in trade and investment.
</P>
<P>
Dong Suwan, head of a delegation from China's Anhui Province,
the sponsor of the trade center in Maputo, said at the opening
ceremony for the center that his province would do its best to
make the center a bridge of cooperation between Mozambique and
China.
</P>
<P>
Leonardo Simao, the Mozambican Minister for Foreign Affairs
and International Cooperation attended the opening ceremony with
about 70 other celebrities in Maputo.  
</P>
</TEXT>
