<HEADLINE> Number of Offices of Foreign Firms in Beijing Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 12 (Xinhua) -- The number of offices of foreign
companies in Beijing is increasing, and is not decreasing as some
Chinese papers have reported, today's Economic Daily says.
</P>
<P>
The paper quotes officials from the Beijing Industry and
Commerce Bureau as saying that the city had 6,617 offices of
foreign firms at the end of March this year, compared with 5,612
in 1996 and some 6,300 in October last year.
</P>
<P>
The bureau is in charge of registering those offices, so its
statistics are accurate, the daily says.
</P>
<P>
The recent reports by some newspapers about a "sharp downturn
in the number of foreign offices in Beijing" are untrue, it adds.
</P>
<P>
The daily also quotes the Press Office of the Beijing Municipal
Government as saying that, in the first quarter of this year, 152
more foreign-funded enterprises registered in Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
