<HEADLINE> China's Coal Industry Continues To Be Overstocked This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Coal sales in China will be down
some this year, with demand from the metallurgy, chemical, and
building materials industries slipping, Market Daily reports today.
</P>
<P>
Demand from the power industry is expected to be up 30 million
tons at most, but the rise is far from enough to affect the
overstocked industry, the paper says, and coal exports are
expected to rise only slightly.
</P>
<P>
China will try to hold its coal output at the same level as
last year and will restrict production at small and medium-sized
coal mines, the paper says. 
</P>
