<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Now World's No.1 Sewing Machine Manufacturer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 12 (Xinhua) -- China's position as the world's top
sewing machine manufacturer remains in place, after it produced
around five million sewing machines last year, which is more than
40 percent of the world's output.
</P>
<P>
Exports of sewing machines continued to rise, with the
"Standard" and "Shanggong" brands out in front, with growth of
some 20 percent each, in spite of the financial crisis in
Southeast Asia, according to "International Business".
</P>
<P>
Export earnings also rose by 33 percent from the previous year
from sewing machine parts sales, the paper, which is sponsored by
the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation, reports.
</P>
<P>
The increase in sewing machines exports will continue this
year, it quoted National Bureau for Light Industry officials as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Major sewing machines manufacturers elsewhere in the world have
branches or joint ventures in China, making the country the
world's sewing machine production center as well.
</P>
<P>
There are 49 Sino-foreign or solely foreign-funded enterprises
in the sewing machine business in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
