<HEADLINE> China's Fuzhou Offers More Land for Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Fuzhou, capital of east China's
Fujian Province, will offer 175 lots of land for bidding
investment during a month-long international investment fair
starting late this month.
</P>
<P>
The pieces of land, with a total size of 5,900 ha, are intended
for real estate, industrial and agricultural development,
according to Li Yichun, director of the city land administration
bureau.
</P>
<P>
Fifty-nine pieces of land are located in the inner city and are
therefore for urban renovation while another 20 pieces are
situated in the city's new areas and planned to be developed for
commerce, trade, recreation, housing, and park facilities. The
other lots of land, scattered in eight counties, are for
industrial and agricultural development.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the procedure necessary to approve the land
projects will take no more than eight days.
</P>
<P>
Fuzhou has launched four similar land-for-investment fairs in
recent years. And contracts have been signed for 175 lots of land
with a combined area of 516 ha, with total investment reaching
7.53 billion yuan (some 900 million US dollars).  
</P>
