<HEADLINE> Standard Chartered Bank Gives More Financial Aid to Chinese Auto Maker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Standard Chartered Bank
will provide a package of fund-raising services for China's
largest light-duty automobile manufacturer -- Jiangling Group,
according to an agreement signed by the two sides here today.
</P>
<P>
From now on, Standard Chartered will provide Jiangling with
financial services including letters of credit, loans for working
capital, and forward foreign exchange contracts, the agreement
said. Jiangling's loans from the British bank will therefore rise
from 50 million US dollars to 80 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Industry experts said that today's agreement heralds "a firm
step forward" in the cooperation between Standard Chartered and
Jiangling Group. Last year the two parties, together with Ford
Motor Co. Ltd., developed a commercial vehicle called Transit.
</P>
<P>
Jiangling Group, 30 percent of whose stake is held by Ford,
boasts an annual production capacity of 60,000 vehicles. Chairman
Sun Min noted that Jiangling's production capacity for the Transit
brand can reach 20,000 units in a short period of time and the
vehicles it produces will be sold both in China and overseas.
</P>
<P>
Official estimates have put China's domestic demand for
commercial automobiles at 200,000 units per year. A recent survey
by the State Information Center indicates that Transit has bright
market prospects.  
</P>
</TEXT>
