<HEADLINE> Automatic Railway Ticket Machine Installed in Nanchang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Automatic ticket machines have
been installed at the railway station in Nanchang, capital of
east China's Jiangxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The ticket machines' software, the first of its kind in China,
has been developed jointly by the railway station and the Nanchang
branch of the Industrial and Commercial Bank of China, the
country's largest bank.
</P>
<P>
Passengers with cards issued by the bank and railway ticket
cards can touch the machine screen and buy any tickets for 85
pairs of trains from Nanchang to elsewhere in China.
</P>
<P>
The introduction of ticket machines has not only provided
passengers with easy accesses but also helped to reduce workload
and accelerate fund settlements, experts said.
</P>
<P>
The Nanchang Railway Bureau has decided to extend the automatic
ticketing machine network to 25 railway stations under its
jurisdiction within this year.
</P>
<P>
Nanchang is the only provincial capital on the Beijing-Kowloon
route, one of China's busiest north-south railway arteries.
</P>
</TEXT>
