<HEADLINE> Pudong's Quarterly Economic Growth Hits 13.3 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's Pudong New Area, a
rising finance and trade zone, reported steady economic growth in
the first three months of this year, official figures indicate.
</P>
<P>
The latest statistics show that Pudong's gross domestic product
rose by 13.3 percent in the first quarter, with the growth rate
standing at 7.1 percent for January and 12.1 percent for the first
two months.
</P>
<P>
Experts acknowledged that Pudong's economic growth momentum is
continuing to consolidate.
</P>
<P>
An analysis shows that the service sector provided a major
backing for Pudong's solid economic growth in the first
quarter. The sector's three-month incremental value soared 22
percent to 5.2 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Pudong's industrial output value was more than 28 billion yuan
(3.37 billion US dollars) for the January-March period, an
increase of 2.4 billion yuan over the same period of last year.
