<HEADLINE> Nigeria Begins Repair of Hydropower Stations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria has begun to repair all its
seven hydropower stations nationwide in a bid to save the
collapsing power supply system in the West African country.
</P>
<P>
Chief Olukunle Oluwasanmi, the Minister of State for Power and
Steel, disclosed this Monday in Osogbo, during a courtesy call on
the Osun State Administrator, Lieutenant Colonel Anthony Obi.
</P>
<P>
"The government is aware of the hardship people are facing
and I want to assure you that work have resumed in earnest and
within the next seven months, all the problems will be things of
the past," the minister of state said. 
</P>
