<HEADLINE> ASOCIO General Assembly to Be Held in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia will host this year's
Asian-Oceanian Computing Industry Organization (ASOCIO) general
assembly and symposium, it was announced here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The assembly and symposium to be held here on November 25 and
26 will focus on discussing information technology (IT) industry
challenges, the shaping of IT investments and the setting up of
smart partnerships and strategic alliances, according to the
Association of Computer Industry Malaysia (known as PIKOM), the
host of the events.
</P>
<P>
The events will be a stepping stone for local companies to
venture into IT businesses in the region and allow them to
network and offer their products to other countries in the
region," PIKOM Chairman Shaifulbahrim Saleh told a media briefing
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Senior officials of 3,000 IT companies from 15 ASOCIO members,
including 300 to 400 IT industry captains, are expected to attend
the events, Shaifulbahrim said, adding that "You can look for the
right person, get the right advice and find the right partner."
</P>
<P>
Shaifulbahrim said that based on ASOCIO's IT Market Report
1997, the total ASOCIO IT market in 1996 was worth about 170.8
billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
ASOCIO was established in Tokyo, Japan, in 1984 to promote,
encourage and foster relationships between the members and to
develop the computing industry in the Asian and Oceanian region.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia last hosted the ASOCIO general assembly and symposium
in 1991. 
</P>
</TEXT>
