<HEADLINE> China Seriously Concerned About Indian Nuclear Test </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 12 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government is seriously
concerned about the nuclear test conducted by India, Chinese
Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao said here today.
</P>
<P>
Zhu made the remarks when asked to comment on India's recent
nuclear test.
</P>
<P>
He said that progress has been gradually made in the
process of nuclear arms reduction, with the Treaty on the
Non-Proliferation of Nuclear Weapons being prolonged indefinitely
and the Comprehensive Nuclear Test Ban Treaty being reached.
</P>
<P>
Under such circumstances, Zhu said, India's conducting of
nuclear test runs against international trend and is detrimental
to the peace and stability of the South-Asian region. 
</P>
