<HEADLINE> U.N. Secretary-General to Meet Iraqi Vice Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 12 (Xinhua) -- United Nations Secretary-General
Kofi Annan will meet here on Tuesday with Iraqi Vice Prime
Minister Tarik Aziz, U.N. officials said in Paris.
</P>
<P>
Annan, who is on a three-day visit here, will make a statement
after the meeting.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first meeting between Annan and Aziz when the
U.N. secretary-general signed an agreement on the U.N. inspection
of Iraqi presidential sites with Aziz in Baghdad on February 23.
</P>
<P>
They will discuss the implementation by Iraq of the agreement
and Aziz is expected to raise the issue of lifting U.N. sanctions
against his country which have been extended by the U.N. Security
Council for six months.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the U.S. CNN television last week, Annan
said that he was "personally very satisfied with the cooperation
of Iraqi authorities since February 23," when he and Aziz signed
the memorandum.
</P>
<P>
As a result of the memorandum, an imminent U.S. military strike
against Iraq was avoided and U.N. inspectors were allowed to enter
Iraq's presidential sites. 
</P>
