<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed broadly lower in thin trading Tuesday
due to the lack of fresh impetus to boost interest.
</P>
<P>
Most investors preferred to stay on the sideline as worries
regarding corporate failures and regional uncertainties remained,
a dealer said.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index fell 10.88
points to 569.17, the all-share Emas Index shed 2.46 points to
144.03, the Industrial Index shed 4.21 points to 1,080.94 and the
Second Board Index lost 1.06 points to 124.22.
</P>
<P>
Losers outpaced gainers by 508 to 154, while 90 counters were
unchanged and 165 others untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover stood at 96.791 million shares worth 260.158
million ringgit (about 68.282 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover dropped to 83.778 million shares worth
239.695 million ringgit (about 62.912 million U.S. dollars) from
90.398 million shares valued at 271.632 million ringgit (about
71.294 million U.S. dollars) last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover increased to 13.013 million shares
worth 20.462 million ringgit (about 5.37 million U.S. dollars)
from last Friday's 10.349 million shares valued at 15.266 million
ringgit (about 4.006 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off-market volume shrunk to 2.289 million shares worth 10.913
million ringgit (about 2.864 million U.S. dollars) from 14.477
million shares valued at 20.770 million ringgit (about 5.451
million U.S. dollars) last Friday.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 4.590
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products 7.138
million shares, construction 7.471 million shares, trading/service
25.871 million shares, infrastructure 525,000 shares, finance
16.185 million shares, hotels 232,000 shares, properties 8.677
million shares, plantation 5.040 million shares, mining 587,000
shares, trusts 43,000 shares, closed/fund 70,000 shares and loans
7.349 million shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
