<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dengue Fever Kills 780 in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Dengue fever, a cholera-like
disease, had killed 780 people as of May 8 in Indonesia, showed
statistics issued by the Ministry of Health.
</P>
<P>
Over 33,000 people had been infected by the disease in 16
provinces of the country since mid January this year, leading
local newspapers Tuesday quoted the statistics as saying.
</P>
<P>
Jakarta, capital of Indonesia, has been worst hit by a dengue
fever this year. As of May 8, the death toll in the city had
reached 78, while some 9,488 had been hospitalized.
</P>
<P>
However, the dengue fever epidemic is showing signs of abating,
deputy governor in charge of social welfare, Djailani said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The number of people admitted to hospitals for the disease has
significantly dropped thanks to government-sponsored fumigation
against the virus carrier, the mosquitoes, he said.
</P>
<P>
"The campaign should go on to eradicate the mosquitoes,
although I'm not that optimistic that the disease can be totally
eradicated," Djailani said.
</P>
<P>
Dengue fever, an acute tropical disease transmitted by
mosquitoes, leaves its victims with fever, rash and severe pains
in the joints and back.
</P>
<P>
Last year, a dengue fever killed 240 people and afflicted
13,207 others in Indonesia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980512.0123 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Stronger Ahead of Budget </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, May 12 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar closed
stronger ahead of the release of the federal budget Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
Colonial State Bank foreign exchange dealer Nick Volanakis said
the Australian dollar had a strong move-up overnight in New York
to 63.90 U.S. cents, before slipping back from that level.
</P>
<P>
The local unit closed at 63.56 U.S. cents, up from 63.36 U.S.
cents Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Volanakis said the market had been generally bearish over the
past few days.
</P>
<P>
"Ahead of the budget there has been a bit of a square-up," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Volanakis said early selling was seen out of Europe, with the
fear of lower growth estimates from the budget.
</P>
<P>
Also putting downward pressure on the Australian dollar from
Monday night's highs was a weakening in the Japanese yen against
the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
But Volanakis said there was good support for the Australian
dollar seen around Monday's lows of 63.22 U.S. cents.
</P>
<P>
Treasurer Peter Costello Tuesday said the value of the
Australian dollar had been remarkably stable for a long time
despite the Asian crisis, pointing to the stability of the trade
weighted index which measures the Australian dollar against the
currencies of the country's major trading partners.
</P>
<P>
"We have a currency that responds to external events and in
trade-weighted terms it has been remarkably stable over a long
period of time," he told reporters.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar was at 84.65 from 83.98 against the
Japanese yen, and at 1.1298 from 1.1202 Against Deutsche mark.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
