proposal for another summit meeting among China, Russia,
Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan and Tajikistan, Chinese Foreign Ministry
spokesman Zhu Bangzao said at a news conference here today.
</P>
<P>
He said China, Russia and the three central Asian countries
held summit meetings in Shanghai in 1996 and in Moscow in
1997. The five countries signed agreements on "Confidence
Building" and "Mutual Arms Reduction in the Border Areas."
</P>
<P>
Zhu said President Nazarbayev of Kazakhstan has proposed
several times that the heads of the five states hold a third
meeting to discuss issues of regional security and economic
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
China believes enhanced cooperation among the five neighboring
countries is in accord with the interests of the peoples of these
countries and benefits the peace, stability and development in the
region, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
China is willing to make concerted efforts to ensure that
positive results come out of a third summit meeting, he said.
