under the old planned economy can't meet the needs of a changed
economic situation both between the two nations and in the world
as a whole.
</P>
<P>
China is willing to expand its trade with Bulgaria, and will
encourage domestic companies to set up new enterprises in the
eastern European country or buy shares of its enterprises, Shi
said, adding that China is also ready to make joint efforts with
Bulgaria to explore international markets.
</P>
<P>
Vasilev said he welcomes Chinese investment in Bulgaria, and
that he will provide them with assistance.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, Chinese and Bulgarian entrepreneurs held an
economic and trade seminar in which Bulgarian President Petar
Stoyanov delivered a speech.
</P>
<P>
After the seminar, Yu Xiaosong, president of the China Council
for Promotion of International Trade, and Bojidar Bojinov,
president of the Chamber of Industry and Commerce of Bulgaria,
signed an agreement on cooperation.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, China and Bulgaria will maintain an
exchange of delegations, hold routine exhibitions and seminars in
Beijing or Sofia, and increase information exchanges.  
