<HEADLINE> Bank of International Settlement to Open Office in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 12 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of International
Settlement (BIS) will set up a representative office in Hong Kong
in July this year as agreements have been inked, the Hong Kong
Monetary Authority (HKMA) announced here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Shang Fulin, deputy governor of the People's Bank of China,
China's central bank, signed the Host Country Agreement with
Alfons Verplaetse, president of the BIS, in Basel on Monday. The
Host Country Agreement grants privileges and immunities to the BIS
in accordance with international practice.
</P>
<P>
Joseph Yam, chief executive of the HKMA, signed the Memorandum
of Administrative Arrangements on behalf of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR). This document lays down the
arrangements for implementing in Hong Kong the privileges and
immunities granted by China.
</P>
<P>
According to the HKMA, senior government officials, central
bank governors and prominent guests from the financial community
will be invited to the official opening of the BIS representative
office, scheduled for July 1998.
</P>
<P>
It will be the first overseas office for the BIS, headquartered
in Basel, Switzerland. The opening of the office will reinforce
the status of Hong Kong as a leading international financial
center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
