<HEADLINE> Rejection of Taiwan by WHO Supports One China Policy, Spokesman Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 12 (Xinhua)-- The United Nations and most
countries have recognized that there is only one China in the
world, Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao said at a
news conference today.
</P>
<P>
Zhu made the remarks when commenting on the World Health
Organization's (WHO) recent rejection of Taiwan as a member.
</P>
<P>
He said that there is only one China in the world and the
government of the People's Republic of China is the sole legal
government of China with Taiwan being an inalienable part of
China.
</P>
<P>
This has been accepted by the United Nations and most
countries, and the stance of WHO is further evidence, he added.
