<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhu Rongji Meets Bulgarian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 12 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government treasures
its ties with Bulgaria, and respects the country's internal and
external policies and the development road the people have chosen
according to their own circumstances, Premier Zhu Rongji said here
today.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting here with visiting Bulgarian President Petar
Stoyanov, Zhu said President Jiang Zemin and Stoyanov had an
in-depth and friendly talks Monday and reached consensus on
a wide range of major issues.
</P>
<P>
"I believe that your excellency's current visit will serve to
increase our mutual understanding, deepen the traditional friendly
relations between the peoples of the two countries and continue to
push ahead bilateral friendly cooperative relations," he said.
</P>
<P>
The premier said traditional friendship exists between the two
nations and for many years the mutually beneficial cooperation and
deep friendship between the people of the two countries have
progressed steadily despite the changeable international situation.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese government is ready to join Bulgaria to bring a
long-term, stable and comprehensive Sino-Bulgarian relationship
into the coming century in line with the principles of mutual
respect, benefit and equality," Zhu added.
</P>
<P>
Stoyanov said the two countries have maintained a lasting
traditional friendship and have a basis for wide-ranging
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria is willing to develop a long-term, cooperative
partnership with China, he said, adding that this is not a
temporary plan but the consensus of all Bulgarian political forces.
</P>
<P>
His ongoing China visit will further enhance friendly
cooperation between the two countries, Stoyanov said.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, both sides exchanged views on further
expanding bilateral economic and trade relations.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said the Chinese government is willing to continue
expanding its economic and trade cooperation with Bulgaria on the
basis of equality and mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
At present, he said, both nations are undertaking economic
reforms and the governmental functions are also undergoing drastic
changes.
</P>
<P>
Both sides should explore new means of cooperation, he said,
adding that he hoped both governments encourage powerful and
reputable companies of both countries to start joint ventures,
solely funded firms or to collaborate in opening a third-country
market to expand bilateral economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Stoyanov said China has leading the world in economic reform,
and that the country is now enjoying the fruits of its
accomplishments.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria, with a good geographic location, is also undertaking
economic reform, and this provides an opportunity for the two
countries to strengthen bilateral economic and trade cooperation,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Stoyanov stressed that Bulgaria is ready to closely cooperate
with China in the economic and trade sectors, and that all
departments and regions should also improve their contacts.
</P>
<P>
He said he believed that, with the concerted effort of both
sides, bilateral economic and trade cooperation would achieve new
progress.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Stoyanov briefed Zhu on the economic
situation in Bulgaria. Zhu said he was pleased with the economic
achievements of Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
Zhu also discussed China's reform and opening-up with Stoyanov,
who left today for Shanghai.  
</P>
</TEXT>
