<HEADLINE> Construction Boom Increases Demand for Asphalt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 12 (Xinhua) -- China's boom in road and housing
construction is likely to cause an unprecedented high demand for
asphalt this year, but asphalt producers may have trouble meeting
the demand, said a latest issue of Market Daily.
</P>
<P>
Asphalt for road use is priced at 1,160-to-1,550 yuan per ton
after several rounds of price hikes, the paper reported.
</P>
<P>
Demand for asphalt for road use is expected to rise to
500,000-to-600,000 tons this year.
</P>
<P>
North China and east China are the main areas with an increased
asphalt demand. The rest of the country will use less asphalt and
more cement for road construction, the paper reported.  
</P>
</TEXT>
