<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 12 (Xinhua) -- The Publicity Department of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee and the Ministry
of Education have issued a circular requiring that all
universities and colleges across the country offer a course on
Deng Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
The circular notes that many institutions of higher learning
have started such a course in recent years, with the compilation
of teaching materials and the preparation of many good teachers.
</P>
<P>
Summing up the experience of teaching reforms, the ministry has
decided to readjust the courses on Marxist theory and ethics, and
to open an independent course on Deng Xiaoping Theory, according
to the circular.
</P>
<P>
The ministry requires that all universities and colleges offer
the course this fall when a new semester begins.
</P>
<P>
The Publicity Department and the ministry have demanded that
priority be put on selecting teachers with good political
awareness to teach the course. In the meantime, teaching materials
should be compiled and teaching methods be improved so that
students can apply the theory in practice.
</P>
<P>
The department and ministry have also urged local publicity
departments and presidents of universities and colleges to promote
the course and supervise the teaching. 
</P>
