<HEADLINE> Mig-21 of Indian Air Force Crashes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 12 (Xinhua) -- A Mig-21 plane belonging to the
Indian Air Force crashed Tuesday into a cluster of shops in
Pathankot district of the Northwest state of Punjab, reports
reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft, which was on a normal training mission, broke in
mid-air into three pieces, one of which fell on the premises of a
shop dealing with iron-scrap, killing four employees.
</P>
<P>
The pilot of the aircraft bailed out but received injuries and
was admitted to a local military hospital.
</P>
<P>
Another piece of the fighter plane hurtled down on the premises
of a scooter dealer causing fire in an adjacent oil depot.
</P>
<P>
However, sources from the Defense Ministry in New Delhi said
that only two people were killed and an equal number injured in
the crash. 
