<HEADLINE> Cableway for Tourists Operational in National Forest Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, May 12 (Xinhua) -- A cableway went into operation today
at Taibai National Forest Park in northwest China's Shaanxi
Province.
</P>
<P>
It starts at the Xiaban Temple (2,800 meters above sea level)
and runs to Shangban Temple (3,200 meters above sea level), with a
straight-cable distance of 1,100 meters. It has 90 cars and can
carry 3,000-to-4,000 persons per day.
</P>
<P>
The park and a local company raised 8.2 million yuan to build
the cable-car system and improve tourist services at this
2,949-hectare sightseeing spot at 3,767.2-meter Taibai Mountain,
the country's highest east of the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau.
</P>
<P>
With the cableway, tourists can reach the mountain peak
conveniently and enjoy the beautiful natural scenery without
climbing the icy paths.  
</P>
