<HEADLINE> Law Lecture for Senior Chinese Officials Held </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Senior Chinese officials attended a
lecture today on financial security and improvement of the legal
system in the financial sector.
</P>
<P>
Senior leaders Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Zhu Rongji, Hu Jintao, Wei
Jianxing and Li Lanqing along with Communist Party and government
officials were present at the lecture given by Cao Jianming, a
professor with the East China College of Political Science and Law.
</P>
<P>
The professor talked about financial security and economic and
state security, the prevention of a financial crisis in various
countries by means of law and relevant legislation on financial
supervision, and hidden domestic peril in the financial sector. In
the meantime, Cao put forward some suggestions on safeguarding
financial security in China.
</P>
<P>
After hearing the lecture, Jiang Zemin, Chinese president and
general secretary of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central
Committee, said that crimes and offenses in the financial sector
must be cracked down on through better legislation, stricter law
enforcement, tighter supervision and more publicity on financial
knowledge.
</P>
<P>
He called on Party and government officials to raise their
awareness about the importance of financial work in the national
economy, and make more of an effort to carry out central decisions
in this regard. In addition, he urged officials to acquire more
financial knowledge and financial laws.
</P>
<P>
After the Asian financial crisis, China won widespread praise
from the international community for its responsible attitude and
making some key moves to give possible assistance to countries hit
by the crisis, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Following financial crises in Asia and other areas of the
world, the governments in various countries have put more emphasis
on preventing and dissolving a financial crisis and safeguarding
financial security, he said.
</P>
<P>
China has made marked progress in financial laws, however, the
legal system still needs to be perfected, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
This was the seventh lecture on laws held for senior
officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
