<HEADLINE> Kuwait Stock Exchange Index Down 20.9 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, May 12 (Xinhua) -- The index of Kuwait Stock
Exchange market slipped 20.9 points to close at 2,304.5 points
Tuesday, compared with 2,325.4 points Monday.
</P>
<P>
The market rebounded by 3.5 points Monday after a continuous
drop in the first two days of this trading week starting last
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The volume, transactions and value all showed decline Tuesday
with a total of 85.662 million shares being changed hands over
2,278 transactions, compared with 121.434 million shares traded
over 2,726 transactions Monday.
</P>
<P>
The value of the shares traded also dropped to 24.146 million
Kuwaiti dinars (79.68 million U.S. dollars), compared with 34.455
million Kuwaiti dinars (113.7 million dollars) Monday.
</P>
<P>
All the sectors showed a down trend in trading with the real
estate sector registering the worst decline, followed by the
sectors of insurance, investment, industrial and banking.
</P>
<P>
A total of 78 listed companies and mutual funds are trading
their shares in Kuwait Stock Exchange. 
</P>
</TEXT>
