<HEADLINE> India Prolongs Retirement Age of Govt Employees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 12 (Xinhua) -- India's cabinet decided Tuesday
to prolong the retirement age of central government employees from
58 to 60 years, Finance Ministry sources said.
</P>
<P>
The decision is expected to benefit some 2.87 million employees
nationwide, saving about 52 billion rupees (1.385 billion U.S.
dollars) for the government.
</P>
<P>
About 70 percent of the 4.1 million government employees would
stand to benefit from the decision, while the remaining 30 percent
are already due to retire at the age of 60. 
</P>
