<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment in Pakistan Totals 640 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investment in Pakistan,
both direct and portfolio, amounted to 639.9 million U.S. dollars
in the first three quarters of the 1997-98 fiscal year (July
1-June 30).
</P>
<P>
This shows a slight improvement in the private foreign
investment inflow, when compared with the investment in the
corresponding period of the previous fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
According to the figures released Tuesday by the State Bank of
Pakistan, the foreign investment inflow during the first quarters
of the current fiscal year showed an increase in portfolio
investment but a decline in direct investment.
</P>
<P>
Out of the total investment inflow of 639.9 million dollars,
the foreign direct investment has accounted to 436.1 million
dollars whereas the share of portfolio investment is 203.8 million
dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to the figures, investment in the power sector during
the first three quarters of the 1997-98 fiscal year remained the
highest with 148.6 million dollars despite a decline from 183.8
million dollars in the corresponding period of the previous fiscal
year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, there has been a substantial increase in the private
investment inflow in mining, quarrying, oil and gas sector,
textile, chemical, pharmaceutical and fertilizers as well as
construction.  
</P>
</TEXT>
