<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng Meets Bulgarian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 12 (Xinhua) -- China is willing to continue its
friendly exchanges and mutually beneficial cooperation oriented
toward the 21st century with Bulgaria on the basis of mutual
respect, benefit and non-interference in each other's internal
affairs, pledged Li Peng in a meeting here today with visiting
Bulgarian President Petar Stoyanov.
</P>
<P>
Li, chairman of the Standing Committee of the Chinese National
People's Congress (NPC), recalled his visit to Bulgaria in 1985 as
a pleasant one and said that he was deeply impressed with the
hospitality of the Bulgarian people.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his belief that Stoyanov's visit to China is bound
to advance Sino-Bulgarian friendly and cooperative ties in a
long-term, stable manner.
</P>
<P>
Stoyanov said he has had very good talks and meetings with
Chinese President Jiang Zemin and Premier Zhu Rongji on separate
occasions and in his meeting today with Li.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his conviction that this visit to China would
further strengthen the friendly cooperative ties between the two
countries and the traditional friendship between the people of the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
The Bulgarian government is willing to develop a long-term
partnership of friendly cooperation oriented toward the 21st
century with China, he said. This is also the common understanding
of the various political parties in Bulgaria, he added.
</P>
<P>
Li stressed that China treasures its relations with Bulgaria
and respects the choices of the Bulgarian people and the internal
and external policies adopted by Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
Li said that inter-parliamentary exchanges are an important
part of bilateral relations and that the NPC values the
development of its ties with the Bulgarian Parliament.
</P>
<P>
The frequent exchanges of visits between the leaders of the NPC
and the Bulgarian parliament in recent years have deepened mutual
understanding and promoted the friendly cooperation between the
two countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Stoyanov briefed Li on Bulgaria's economic
situation and its parliament, and Li also informed him of the work
of the NPC.
</P>
<P>
The NPC is the most powerful body of China with legislation and
supervision being its two major functions, Li said. The NPC and
its standing committee both supervise and support the work of
government, the Supreme People's Court and the Supreme People's
Procuratorate, he said, adding that supervision and support
complement each other.  
</P>
</TEXT>
