Currency Unions (435,000 U.S. dollars) for the 1998 international
campaign to set up the ICC court. (EU-ICC-Backing)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Dengue fever, a cholera-like disease, had killed
780 people as of May 8 in Indonesia, showed statistics issued by
the Ministry of Health.
</P>
<P>
Over 33,000 people had been infected by the disease in 16
provinces of the country since mid January this year, leading
local newspapers Tuesday quoted the statistics as saying.
</P>
<P>
Jakarta, capital of Indonesia, has been worst hit by a dengue
fever this year. As of May 8, the death toll in the city had
reached 78, while some 9,488 had been hospitalized.
(Indonesia-Dengue Fever)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has
advanced his trip to Washington to meet with U.S. Secretary of
State Madeleine Albright up to Wednesday from Thursday, it was
announced here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Albright invited Netanyahu for a meeting during their
telephone conversation Monday night and Netanyahu revised his
U.S. travel plans, advancing the departure time from Thursday to
early Wednesday morning, Netanyahu's office said.
(Israel-Netanyahu-U.S. Trip)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic Monday
rebuffed another bid by two U.S. envoys to press Belgrade to allow
foreign mediation of the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
Meeting special envoys to the Balkans Richard Holbrooke and
Robert Gelbard here again, Milosevic said, "The policy of pressure
(on his country) must make way for one of cooperation on an equal
footing with mutual confidence."
</P>
<P>
Cooperation was the best way to achieve peace and stability,
and develop economic and cultural ties in the Balkans, Tanjug news
agency quoted Milosevic as saying. (Yugoslavia-US-Kosovo)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
