<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania Stages War Exercises With Foreign Forces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Romanian armed forces will stage
a number of joint war exercises in Romania with forces from other
countries.
</P>
<P>
Approval came at a joint conference on Tuesday between
Romania's two parliaments, a Romania News Agency report said.
</P>
<P>
In the coming four months, forces from Romania, France and the
United States will exercise in Romanian territory. Exercises
include one scheduled from June 5 to 9.
</P>
<P>
Thirty French paratroopers will take part in a planned airborne
manoeuvre in the south of Romania from June 11 to 15.
</P>
<P>
These exercises are planned under the framework of bilateral
cooperation agreements, and under the defense ministry's foreign
exchange programs, the Romanian Defense Committee said in its
report to parliament.
</P>
<P>
Seeking early membership to the North Atlantic Treaty
Organisation (NATO) has been a set policy of Romania in recent
years. The country's military diplomacy includes promoting
military cooperation with the NATO and the alliance's member
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
