<HEADLINE> Chinese State Councillor Meets Wife of Namibian PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese State Councillor Wu Yi met
here today with Loine Geingos, wife of Namibian Prime Minister
Hage Geingob.
</P>
<P>
Wu said the frequent high-level visits between China and
Namibia in recent years have improved bilateral economic and trade
ties.
</P>
<P>
The bilateral trade volume is not large, but China has set up a
dozen joint ventures in the African country, Wu said, adding that
the two countries enjoy broad potential in economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
China is willing to develop friendly ties with Namibia on the
basis of equality and mutual benefit, Wu said. She stressed that
China, although a developing country, will continue to assist
Namibia's economic construction within its capacity.
</P>
<P>
Geingos said she appreciated China's assistance in its
independence and country-building, and that she hopes Chinese
enterprises invest in her country.
</P>
<P>
Geingos arrived here as a guest of the Chinese People's
Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
