<HEADLINE> China Sets New Goal in Helping Disabled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 12 (Xinhua) -- China aims to help its impoverished
disabled out of poverty in three years by making sure they have
enough food and clothing.
</P>
<P>
More specifically, the per capita net income of every poor
family with a handicapped member or members in China must reach
the basic livelihood level set by the local government by 2000.
</P>
<P>
The new goal is incorporated into the 1998-2000 plan to help
the disabled out of poverty drafted by a poverty-relief task force
under the State Council, the central bank, the Ministry of
Finance, and the China Disabled Persons' Federation, which was
made public at a national video conference held today.
</P>
<P>
Disabled persons account for one-third of China's
poverty-stricken population, which is believed to be 58 million.
</P>
</TEXT>
