<HEADLINE> Rafter Defeated in Italian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Dutch substitute Sjeng Schalken
toppled fourth-seeded Patrick Rafter on Tuesday to reach the
second round of the 2.45 million U.S. dollars Italian Open tennis
tournament.
</P>
<P>
Schalken who replaced injured Swiss Marc Rosset an hour before
the tournament, scored a 6-4, 6-7 (4/7), 6-4 upset over the
unlucky Australian in more than two hours.
</P>
<P>
Rafter, U.S. Open champion, saved five match points in the
final set before acknowledging his defeat to Schalken who ranked
57th on the ATP Tour.
</P>
<P>
It was the Australian's first clay court match of the year.
</P>
<P>
Former French Open champion sixth-seeded Yevgeny Kafelnikov of
Russia knocked out Swede Thomas Johansson 7-6 (7/5), 6-2 to
advance further.
</P>
<P>
In other matches involving unseeded players, New Zealand's
Brett Steven beat France's Guillaume Raoux 7-5, 6-2, Spaniard
Albert Costa ousted Hernan Gumy of Argentina 6-3, 6-1 while
compatriot Fernando Vicente beat German Marc Goellner 2-6, 6-3,
6-1.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, No. 2 Petr Korda, fifth-ranked Greg Rusedski and
No. 7 Jonas Bjorkman were all eliminated in the first round.
</P>
</TEXT>
