<HEADLINE> China, UK Sign MOU on Health Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, May 12 (Xinhua) -- The People's Republic of China and the
United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland signed here
Tuesday a Memorandum of Understanding on Health Cooperation between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Under the MOU signed by Chinese Health Minister Zhang Wenkang and
his British counterpart Ms Tessa Jowell, the main areas of
cooperation will be:
</P>
<P>
- infectious diseases, non-infectious disease, the application of
epidemiology, health promotion and social medicine;
</P>
<P>
-delivery of health care (with particular attention to primary
health care, maternal and child health, geriatrics, dentistry, the
care of people with epilepsy, and hospital management);
</P>
<P>
- nutrition;
</P>
<P>
- traditional Chinese medicine.
</P>
<P>
Other fields of cooperation may also take place by mutual consent,
says the MOU, which came into effect on January 1, 1998 and is valid
until December 31, 2000.
</P>
<P>
Under the MOU, the two countries will have exchanges of
specialists of a total of 60 man-weeks from each side and
information in the above-mentioned fields. 
</P>
</TEXT>
