<HEADLINE> 2 Israeli Soldiers Wounded in Northern Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Two Israeli soldiers were wounded in
northern Israeli area Galilee Monday night when Lebanese Hezbollah
guerrillas unleashed a series of mortar barrages on Israeli
positions along the border, Lebanon's Daily Star newspaper
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
They were the first casualties on Israeli territory for more
than two years.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian-backed Hezbollah said the attack served as a
warning to the Israeli army and implied that if the Israelis
continue to claim civilian casualties, Hezbollah's resistance may
step up operations deeper into the Jewish state, according to the
paper.
</P>
<P>
The attacks came hours after two Lebanese civilians were
wounded by Israeli artillery in Kfar Tibnit, about 15 kilometers
from the Israeli border, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
A school and a car were damaged in the shelling, which also
targeted other nearby villages, it added.
</P>
<P>
The casualties brought to 53 the number of Israeli soldiers
wounded so far this year. Four have been killed.
</P>
<P>
Since Israel set up a 1,200-square-kilometer buffer zone in
south Lebanon in 1985 with the aim to protect its northern area
from Lebanese guerilla cross-border attacks, Lebanon's resistance
led by Hezbollah has been engaging in a war trying to dislodge
some 2,000 Israeli occupying forces from Lebanon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
