<HEADLINE> Copper Price Falls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, May 12 (Xinhua) -- The price of copper on the London
metal exchange market declined by 33 U.S Cents per pound in the
first quarter of this year compared with the same period of last
year.
</P>
<P>
The average price per pound dropped to 77 Cents in the first
quarter of this year from 110 Cents in the same quarter of last
year, according to Zambia Daily Mail.
</P>
<P>
The national newspaper quoted the monthly Real Sector report
for May as reporting that the lowest price was 75.51 Cents
recored in February while the highest was 79.29 Cents in March.
</P>
<P>
Zambia Consolidated Copper Mines (ZCCM) produced 56,000 tons
of copper and the newly privatized Roan Antelope Mining
Corporation of Zambia produced 8,500 tons of copper in the first
quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
Copper production at ZCCM continued to be constrained by
technical problems arising from lack of investment and
uncertainty surrounding the privatization of Nkana and Nchanga
mines.
</P>
<P>
The negotiations over the sale of the two biggest copper mines
in the copper-producing country collapsed last month due to
disagreement on the price of the two divisions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
