<HEADLINE> More Young People Eager to Join The Communist Party </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 12 (Xinhua) -- A recent Shanghai survey found that
more university students there have expressed an interest in
applying for membership in the Communist Party, today's Wenhui
Daily reports.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Institute of Foreign Trade asked students at Fudan
University, East China Teachers' University, and East China
University of Science and Engineering and found that 81 percent of
the respondents expressed a desire to apply and that most
explained their enthusiasm by saying that "it is a better way to
serve the motherland and the people."
</P>
<P>
Others said that being a Party member is an honor and that they
didn't want to fall behind their fellow students.
</P>
<P>
Of those who said they have no intention to join the CPC, 40
percent said they thought they were not qualified to be a Party
member, but the corruption that exists among some Party members
was another reason given for their holding back.
</P>
<P>
Among parents surveyed, 62 percent said they would support
their son or daughter in joining the Communist Party.
</P>
<P>
The study also found that students are paying more attention to
domestic and international news and that most had read articles on
Deng Xiaoping Theory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
