<HEADLINE> China Praised for Taking A Constructive Stance on World Affairs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Former foreign minister of the
Republic of Korea (ROK) Han Sung-Joo said at a recent workshop on
"China and the World in the 21st Century" that China has
established interdependent and friendly relations with the ROK and
the rest of Asia.
</P>
<P>
He said that in the recent financial crisis in Asia, China
actively provided currency assistance to some badly stricken
countries and managed to maintain the stability of its own
currency, thereby contributing enormously to Stablizing the Asian
economy.
</P>
<P>
China's policies have benefited other countries of the world,
and China has already established interdependent and friendly
relations with the Republic of Korea and the rest of Asia, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also praised China for taking a "constructive and
cooperative stance" not only on the question of the Korean
Peninsula, but also in Asia and other parts of the world.
</P>
<P>
The former foreign minister, who is now a professor at Korean
University, expressed his confidence in China's new leadership in
accelerating the market-oriented reform and opening-up.
</P>
<P>
This in turn will have a positive effect on the Korean
Peninsula, he said.
</P>
<P>
According to Han, it is high time for the ROK to upgrade its
relations with China to the level with the United States and
Japan. 
