<HEADLINE> Train Accidents in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, May 12 (Xinhua) -- A train derailed Monday evening in
Bangladesh, disrupting the rail communication between Dhaka and
the southeastern seaport city of Chittagong, press reports said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred at about 6 p.m. local time (1200 GMT)
when the engine of a Chittagong-bound express from the capital
derailed soon after leaving Imamabari station, Brahmanbaria
district, some 80 kilometers northeast of Dhaka.
</P>
<P>
No casualty was reported so far.
</P>
<P>
This was the second train accident in 38 hours in the country.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, a Chittagong-bound passenger train rammed into cargo
carriages in eastern Comilla district, which had been reportedly
disconnected from a Dhaka-bound goods train, killing at least 18
people and injuring 20 others. 
</P>
