<HEADLINE> Cubas Proclaims Victory in Paraguay's Presidential Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, May 11 (Xinhua) -- Paraguay's ruling Colorado
Party candidate Raul Cubas Monday proclaimed his victory in the
presidential elections as preliminary results gave him a 12-point
lead.
</P>
<P>
According to reports from a press conference in the capital
city of Asuncion, Cubas' rival Democratic Alliance candidate
Domingo Laino admitted his defeat and said he would respect and
abide by the election results.
</P>
<P>
With 68.9 percent of the ballots tallied by late afternoon
Monday, Cubas had 54 percent against Laino's 42 percent.
</P>
<P>
The results showed that the Colorado Party, which has governed
this South American nation for more than 50 years, will continue
its administration.
</P>
<P>
They also showed that Cubas' running mate, Colorado Party
President Luis Argana, will become the country's vice-president.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that 2.04 million registered for the elections,
nearly 85 percent of those who registered voted, the highest
turnout in the country's history. 
</P>
