<HEADLINE> Thai Government Guarantees Bank Deposits: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Thai people who put money in banks
or financial firms have no reason to worry since the government
guarantees deposits at all operating firms and commercial banks,
Finance Minister Tarrin Nimmanhaeminda said.
</P>
<P>
Tarrin's Monday speech followed reports that 35 operating
financial firms and some commercial banks have been facing
liquidity problems.
</P>
<P>
He admitted that he had received reports about the liquidity
crunch. but he told the public not to be worried about their
deposits at all operating financial houses as the government had
guaranteed them.
</P>
<P>
The Bangkok Post said Tuesday that the Bank of Thailand, the
country's central bank, reportedly notified the finance minister
that at least three financial institutions and two commercial
banks were in critical condition as they had been hard hit with
deposit runs.
</P>
<P>
However, Tarrin denied the speculation that the government may
not let the remaining financial firms collapse like the 56
cash-strapped firms which had been ordered closed last December.
</P>
<P>
He said it was the responsibility of the shareholders of firms
with tight liquidity to tackle problems by seeking new capital
under the close supervision of the Bank of Thailand.
</P>
<P>
If shareholders failed to boost capital, the ministry would
look into the firms' financial conditions and the central bank's
order about their capital increase.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Tarrin said the stability problem of the financial
sector was the main task for newly appointed central bank governor
Chatumongol Sonakul.
</P>
<P>
Chatumongol received royal appointment last Friday, replacing
Chaiyawat Wibulsawasdi, who was accused of being responsible for
the collapse of the country's economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
