<HEADLINE> Rosin Helps Mountain Dwellers Escape Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Rosin production has helped
200,000 people living in mountainous regions in south China's
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region escape poverty, with related
activities increasing total income in the region by 600 million
yuan.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi, a region blessed with abundant pine forest resources,
produced 270,000 tons of pine resin in 1997. The region processed
210,000 tons of rosin and 30,000 tons of turpentine oil during the
year and recorded a total industrial output value of over 1.2
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The region's forest coverage has grown from 1.7 million
hectares only ten years ago to the current 6.7 million hectares,
including pine forests covering some five million
hectares. Approximately one third of them currently produce pine
rosin.
</P>
<P>
Rosin and turpentine are widely used in the production of paper
making, soap, paint and textiles. The world market demand for
rosin and turpentine has grown by some 5-6 percent annually in
recent years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
