<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> High-Tech Zones Blooming in Northeast China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province is attaching importance to high-tech development zones,
which received 57.77 billion yuan in revenue last year, with
nearly 36 billion yuan from high technology.
</P>
<P>
As an old industrial base focusing on heavy and chemical
industries, Liaoning, which is famous for its traditional
industries, has made an effort to invigorate traditional
industries through technology.
</P>
<P>
An official from the provincial government said Liaoning
province now has three state-level high-tech zones in cities such
as Shenyang, Dalian, and Anshan, and three provincial-level zones
in cities such as Jinzhou, Liaoyang and Yingkou, covering 71.8
square kilometers of land.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning Province approved 110 enterprises to enter high-tech
zones, with 17 projects each having an investment exceeding 20
million U.S. dollars. High-tech zones in Shenyang and Dalian have
established good relations with high-tech zones in foreign
countries.
</P>
<P>
All these high-tech zones nurtured their own pillar industries
and enterprises, and completed 3.85 billion yuan of investment,
with 1.61 billion yuan in infrastructure facilities last year.
</P>
<P>
In the year 1998, all these high-tech zones in Liaoning will
continue to develop high-tech enterprises and pillar products.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
