<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Milosevic Defies U.S. Pressure for Foreign Mediation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, May 11 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic Monday rebuffed another bid by two U.S. envoys to press
Belgrade to allow foreign mediation of the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
Meeting special envoys to the Balkans Richard Holbrooke and
Robert Gelbard here again, Milosevic said, "The policy of pressure
(on his country) must make way for one of cooperation on an equal
footing with mutual confidence."
</P>
<P>
Cooperation was the best way to achieve peace and stability,
and develop economic and cultural ties in the Balkans, Tanjug news
agency quoted Milosevic as saying.
</P>
<P>
Respecting the territorial integrity and non-interference in
other countries' internal affairs was the basis of attaining peace
and stability in the region, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Yugoslav Prime Minister Radoje Kontic said on Monday
that international sanctions against Belgrade would be
counter-productive and make the prospects of a political
settlement more remote.
</P>
<P>
Sanctions and pressure on Yugoslavia "only encourage maximalist
demands by Albanian separatists and terrorists", he warned.
</P>
<P>
Holbrooke and Gelbard, on a shuttle mission to reduce ethnic
tensions in the troubled Serbian province of Kosovo, met
Milosevic, Kosovo ethnic Albanian leader Ibrahim Rugova and
Albanian President Rexhep Meidani and Prime Minister Fatos Nano on
Saturday and Sunday.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, Britain, France, Germany, Italy and the United
States -- but not Russia -- decided to impose an embargo on
investments in Yugoslavia, which includes Serbia and Montenegro.
</P>
<P>
Kosovo, with an ethnic Albanian majority, has sunk into chaos
since ethnic Albanians calling for independence from Serbia
clashed with the local Serb police in February.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav and Serbian authorities have rejected any foreign
involvement or the internationalization of the issue, arguing it
is Serbia's internal affair. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
