<HEADLINE> Slovenian Population Dwindles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zagreb, May 11 (Xinhua) -- Slovenia saw a continuous decline in
its population last year, the state statistical bureau reported
Monday.
</P>
<P>
At the end of 1997, the population of the former Yugoslav
country totaled 1,984,923, or 2,100 less than in 1996.
</P>
<P>
With a gradual drop in birth rate, the population was getting
"older," averaging 38 years old.
</P>
<P>
The country had 48 centenarians at the time, the bureau
said. 
