<HEADLINE> More Handicapped to Be Employed in Northwest China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Gansu Province
plans to employ some 40,000 handicapped workers within the next
three years, equaling the total number hired in the past four
decades.
</P>
<P>
There are 1.2 million disabled persons in the province, making
up nearly 5 percent of the total population. At present, only
40,000 handicapped people have jobs.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has worked out related regulations
and required that disabled persons should account for a ratio of
the total employees in government bodies, institutes and
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The fund used for handicapped persons' poverty relief has been
increased to 6 million yuan annually from 3 million yuan,
according to a provincial official.
</P>
<P>
He added that many employment service centers for the disabled
have been set up across the province to provide information,
training, consultation and various services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
