<HEADLINE> Langfang Attracts Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, May 12 (Xinhua) -- Langfang, a city in north
China's Hebei Province, had attracted 96 projects funded by
domestic and overseas investors by April this year, with total
investments surpassing three billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Langfang has established four provincial-level development
zones since 1992. The initial 13 projects in the Langfang
Development Zone, involving total investments of 596 million yuan,
have entered operations.
</P>
<P>
The 96 projects, which focus on industry, agriculture,
infrastructure facilities, housing and high technology, involve
foreign investments in the form of joint and shareholding ventures.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture projects include a pollution-free cultivation base
established at a cost of 82.7 million yuan and a key state water
conservation project involving a total investment of 28 million
yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Langfang government has also stepped up infrastructure
construction in order to provide high quality services geared to
attracting more foreign investors.  
