<HEADLINE> Thailand's Wild Shrimps Can Go to U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, May 12 (Xinhua) -- The United States is satisfied with
Thailand's performance in saving sea turtles from drowning in
trawling nets, and now allows Thai wild shrimps to access its
market, according to the Thai Foreign Trade Department.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. certified on May 1 that Thailand and 38 other
shrimp-catching nations have measures to save endangered sea
turtles equal to those of the U.S.
</P>
<P>
Thai exporters can export wild shrimps to the U.S. as usual,
Pracha Charutrakulchai, director-general of the department, was
quoted Tuesday by the Bangkok Post as saying.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Commerce Department is empowered to ban imported
products if they are produced in environmentally unsound ways.
</P>
