<HEADLINE> Nigeria Names 25 Players for World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, May 11 (Xinhua) -- The Nigeria Football Association
(NFA) on Monday announced a squad of 25 players for the '98 France
World Cup.
</P>
<P>
Most of the players were selected from the 1996 Olympic
champion team and the 1994 U.S. World Cup squad.
</P>
<P>
The team includes three African footballers -- Kanu Nwankwo,
1996; Rashidi Yekini, 1993; and Victor Ikepeba, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Uche Justine Akubuike, one of the three goalkeepers, is the
only home-based player in the team.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria, the only African country that has won an Olympic
soccer gold medal, boosts many talented players. Though it may not
be among the most powerful competitors for the World Cup, it is
widely believed that Nigeria, in its good shape, could be the
No. 1 dark horse in France this summer.
</P>
<P>
There are, however, warnings that the team may not meet the
high expectations from both home and overseas, as its
overseas-based players have not enough time together and seem not
to care enough about team performance.
</P>
<P>
Goalkeepers (3):
</P>
<P>
Ike Shorunmu, Willy Okpara, Uche Justine Akubuike;
</P>
<P>
Defenders (9):
</P>
<P>
Uche Okechukwu, Taribo West, Mobi Oparaku, Celestine Babayaro,
Jero Shakpoke, Kingsley Obiekwu, Ajibade Babalade, Garba Lawal,
Uche Okafor;
</P>
<P>
Midfielders (5):
</P>
<P>
Sunday Oliseh, Austine Okocha, Karibe Ojigwe, Steven Musa, Godwin
Okpara;
</P>
<P>
Forwards (8):
</P>
<P>
Finidi George, Tijani Babangida, Kanu Nwankwo, Victor Ikepeba,
Danie Amokachi, Rasheed Yekini, Wilson Oruma, Mutiu Adepoju.
</P>
<P>
The players are expected to arrive in Switzerland for camping
by May 23.  
</P>
</TEXT>
