<HEADLINE> Gingrich to Travel to Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 11 (Xinhua) -- U.S. House of Representatives
Speaker Newt Gingrich will travel to Israel at the end of May, as
a gesture to show his different attitude toward the Jewish state
with President Bill Clinton, his spokesman said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
He will go with a U.S. congressional delegation to Israel but
has not plan to visit any Arab countries, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Gingrich's announcement came just when the State Department
said Secretary of State Madeleine Albright would meet with Israeli
Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu on Wednesday to try to revive
the deadlocked Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Gingrich has attacked Clinton's Middle East policy, calling it
favorable to Palestinian positions at the expense of Israel's
security needs.
</P>
<P>
Last Week, he urge Clinton to stop bullying Israel to accept a
peace deal with the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Gingrich also planned to stop in Italy and meet Pope John
Paul. 
